# vantage-ui-examples

A public, **black-box** example catalog + **BDD UI test suite** for the closed-source `vantage-ui`
app. Two jobs: ship runnable example inventories, and prove the published binary opens them clean.

If this file drifts from the repo (new app, new MCP tool, renamed driver), fix it in the same change.

## What this repo is

- The **only** way to control the app is its **MCP API** at `http://127.0.0.1:14488/mcp`. Today the
  app exposes a single tool, **`list_logs`** — richer interaction is blocked on new MCP tools
  (tracked in `todo/scenario-features.md`).
- **Strictly black-box.** Never vendor vantage-ui source. Never add `gpui` or `TestAppContext` here —
  those are vantage-ui's in-process tools and can't drive a published binary.
- Tests launch the **real published binary**, resolved by the launcher in this order: `$VANTAGE_UI_BIN`
  → download+cache from S3 (`https://vantage-releases.s3.eu-west-2.amazonaws.com`, cached under
  `~/.cache/vantage-ui/`) → local `../vantage-ui` release build.

## Layout contract

- `test-framework/` — the reusable engine: `src/{world,launcher,mcp_client}.rs` (lib), the
  **`vantage-ui-test`** driver binary, and the shared steps in `src/steps/`. Shared `*.feature` live
  in `test-framework/features/common/` (currently just `startup.feature`). Never copy shared steps
  per app.
- `apps/<name>/` — one self-contained example: `inventory/` (the YAML catalog), `tests/`
  (app-specific `*.feature`), `README.md`, optional `docs/`.

## The example apps

- **`apps/bakery/`** — CSV-backed, **offline-clean** (no network on startup). The reference app.
- **`apps/spacex/`** — GraphQL against the public SpaceX API; **intentionally not offline-clean**
  (its README says so) — it exercises a live remote datasource.
- **`apps/vantage-github/`** — **self-mutating inventory**: `kind: terminal` actions run `gh` and
  generate/commit inventory files that hot-reload (not ephemeral); uses `chart_type: stacked_area`.

## Inventory layout

`inventory/` holds `datasource/`, `table/`, `page/`, `menu/`, and `action/` YAML (the `action/`
subdir defines row/page actions — all three apps use it now).

## Adding an app

1. Create `apps/<name>/inventory/` with the YAML folders above.
2. Keep it **offline-clean** unless the app is explicitly about a remote source: launching must log no
   ERROR. Prefer a CSV datasource (opens no connection at startup) or a committed, seeded SQLite file.
   A datasource pointing at an unreachable DB logs ERROR and fails the startup test.
3. Add a `README.md`. The shared startup check runs automatically; add `tests/*.feature` only for
   app-specific behaviour.

## Adding a scenario

- Reuse existing steps; add a new step only when none fits. Keep gherkin declarative — logic goes in
  step functions, not feature text.
- Tag not-yet-runnable scenarios `@wip`; the driver filters them out.
- Readiness is signalled by the logs, not the clock: wait for the catalog's `"loaded folder"` INFO
  lines (one per inventory folder kind) — **don't depend on wall-clock timing.**

## Running & quality

- `cargo run -p test-framework -- apps/<name>` (one app) or `-- --all`.
- Set `$VANTAGE_UI_BIN`, or build `../vantage-ui` with `cargo build --release`. The driver sets
  `$VANTAGE_APP_INVENTORY` and `$VANTAGE_MCP_ADDR` for the launched binary.
- Keep `cargo fmt` and `cargo clippy` clean.
- Pin `rmcp` to the **exact** version vantage-ui's MCP server uses (wire compat) — currently
  `=1.7.0`.

## CI

- `.github/workflows/bdd.yaml` — reusable workflow (`workflow_call`) taking `channel` + `version`,
  resolving the binary from S3 and running the suite.
- `bdd-nightly.yaml` / `bdd-stable.yaml` — thin wrappers **dispatched by vantage-ui's nightly and
  release pipelines** after a build publishes. Fire-and-forget; vantage-ui doesn't block its release
  on them. Free CI minutes (public repo).

## Scope discipline

Capture out-of-scope-but-needed work in `todo/*.md`; don't silently expand scope or park unscoped
work in code comments. Commits: single-line, imperative; no `Co-Authored-By: Claude` trailer.

## Related repos

Checked out alongside this one under `~/Work/` — each has its own `.rules`:

- **`vantage-ui`** — the app under test (private repo). New MCP tools / YAML features land there
  first; this repo's scenarios follow. Its release pipeline dispatches this repo's `bdd-*.yaml`.
- **`vantage`** — the data-layer crates (`vantage-*`) the example inventories run against.
- **`vantage-terraform`** — owns the `vantage-releases` bucket the launcher pulls binaries from.
- **`vantage-web2`** — the marketing site; mirrors this repo's examples catalog.
